metadata.name: Slumbers #188
metadata.description:
Generative abstract artwork that explores forms, shapes, coloring and brushwork.

Options:

- press 'f' to turn off paper-like texture (recommended for print on hi-quality paper)
- press 's' to save the PNG image of the current view
- press 1, 2, 3, or 4 to save hi-res PNG images

Colors and textures might differ slightly on some devices due to the heavy use of low alpha blending. Calibrated and tested on Firefox 107.0 & Chrome 107.0.5304.107 on Win10 x64 Intel machine.

Created using p5js.

@VolatileMoods, November, 2022.
tags: slumbers volatile moods abstract generative painting colors brushwork

metadata.name: Strata #281
metadata.description:
A generative series inspired by the work of Vera MolnÃ¡r, Strata explores the diversity that can come from one shape - the simple rectangle.

With 16 properties and ~600 palettes, I hope that each mint offers something unique and special.

Exploration is fully open and will be left open post-mint :)

metadata.name: Yaff #145
metadata.description:
I used this collection to teach my daughter a little bit about generative art. We enjoyed working on it so much that I wanted to share it so she could see it out in the wild.

All primary sales proceeds will be donated to bellyful, a local charity supporting new parents.

Keyboard shortcuts:
"s" - Save hi-res image
"p" - Start/stop animation
"o" - Show/hide particle tails (when animating)

metadata.name: Rough Cuts #225
metadata.description:
Abstract generative artwork that explores composition and form by cutting canvas with straight lines. Coded brushwork gives a real-painting look to each piece.

Options:

- press 's' to save the PNG image of the current view
- press 1, 2, 3, or 4 to save hi-res PNG images

Created using p5js.

@VolatileMoods, July, 2022.

metadata.name: Selvedge #182
metadata.description:
An ode to my print background. 
My love of process flaws, from offsetting to uneven ink coverage. 
A culmination of experience from graphic designer to generative artist.
This is my self portrait of 2021.

tw: philipbell_
ig: philiphunterbell

metadata.name: Wavvve #13
metadata.description:
GLSL painting study, reaching a mix between digital and analog textures.
Available in 5 color pallets, and different feature combinations including an initial animated time until the painting reaches its final form.

November, 2021

metadata.name: FairyCells #38
metadata.description:
FairyCells is a series created by a generative system, displaying shapes, between 1 and 10, made up of three different color palettes. 
Cells cannot cross each other, and are composed of a flat tint and/or a hatch system.

You can right-click to download an SVG file of the NFT or press Â«Â EÂ Â» to export as png (3401x3401px)

Moreover, the digital version can exist as a physical piece.
Owning the NFT gives the right to order, in addition, a 30x30cm plotter drawing of it. More information about it here: https://nft.julienespagnon.fr/fairy-cells.
You can see some test examples plotted in the google form: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1FO3Umh49qmJApZAlQgZ46a2y421QYEWIW8r72nLrW4Q/edit

Work by Julien Espagnon - 2021/2022

metadata.name: Comstractions #27
metadata.description: This collection explores the combination of abstract shapes and comic book styles. Several vintage comic palettes and bold outlines breathe life into abstract superheroes and villains, animals and buildings.

metadata.name: Annum #8013
metadata.description:
This project is being released in celebration of the 1 year aniversary of Achromat, my first release on fxhash. In addition to being inspired by Achromat, aspects of other previous projects have been incorporated. My deepest gratitude to all who have collected my work over the past year.

In live mode, add &size=<YOUR_PIXEL_SIZE> to change the pixel size of the image for export (Right click to save). For example, &size=4000 will set the width of the image to be 4000 pixels.

50% of primary sales go to Savepakistan.

metadata.name: Turpentine #1
metadata.description:
This token generates abstract digital paintings in the style of oil paintings. Brushstrokes are simulated by using noise and random functions. Each painting uses a two-color palette (in rare cases only single color might be used).

- press 's' to save the PNG image of the current view.
- press '1' to save 2400x2400 PNG image
- press '2' to save 4000x4000 PNG image
- press '3' to save 5600x5600 PNG image
- press '4' to save 7200x7200 PNG image

The artwork was created using p5js.

@VolatileMoods

NFT Licence
March 2022.
